The course focuses on culture as a pattern of values, attitudes, beliefs and norms that distinguishes one group of people from another. Different approaches to culture (including Hofstede, Inglehart, Schwartz) and the dimensions most commonly used to describe culture will be introduced. The course provides an overview of how to measure culture and what databases are used for this purpose. The impact of culture on various economic and business phenomena (e.g. entrepreneurship, innovation, corruption, but also communication style, expectations, cooperation, success of new solutions) will be introduced on a scientific basis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course provides an understanding of what culture and cultural differences are and how to take cultural differences into account in economics and business.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student, who has passed the course * understands the nature of culture and knows various well-known theoretical cultural models; * knows how to measure culture, knows the most popular cultural indicators and databases that provide information about culture; * is aware of cultural diversity and is able to detect it; * is able to take into account cultural differences and analyse the impact of different aspects of culture on the economy and business.
